    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Best X Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring X Plays",
    "description": "Master the best X words in Scrabble with ranked list, point values, and strategy tips.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/best-x-words-scrabble" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the best X word in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OXYPHENBUTAZONE scores 41 points as the theoretical best. For practical play, MAXIMIZE scores 28 points, EXACTLY scores 19 points, and HEXAGON/JINX/SPHINX each score 18 points. X is worth 8 points per tile." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best two-letter X words in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "AX, EX, OX, and XI all score 9 points each. These are among the highest-scoring two-letter words in Scrabble and are essential for parallel plays, tight board positions, and reaching premium squares." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should you ever exchange X in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Never exchange X. With four two-letter words available (AX, EX, OX, XI — all scoring 9 points), X always has a valid high-scoring play. Even in the worst position, you can score 9+ points. Hold X and wait for premium square access." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">High-Scoring Words</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Best X Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring X Plays</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        X is arguably the best tile in Scrabble relative to its difficulty. Worth 8 points (third-highest after Q and Z), X doesn't need any specific companion letter and has four two-letter plays as fallbacks. From monster words like MAXIMIZE to surgical strikes with AX or OX, X is the most versatile premium tile in the game.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 10 Best X Words for Scrabble</h2>
      <p>These are the highest-scoring X words, ranked by base point value. X's versatility means you'll find strong plays at every word length.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Length</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">OXYPHENBUTAZONE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">41</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">15</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MAXIMIZE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">28</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EXACTLY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">19</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">HEXAGON</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">JINX</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SPHINX</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">OXYGEN</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">GALAXY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EXOTIC</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PIXEL</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why X Is the Most Versatile Premium Tile</h2>
      <p>X holds a unique position in Scrabble — it's the third most valuable tile at 8 points, but it's arguably the easiest premium tile to play. Unlike Q (which usually needs U) and Z (which has limited two-letter options), X has four two-letter words: AX, EX, OX, and XI. Each scores 9 points, giving you a guaranteed high-scoring fallback in any board position.</p>
      <p>Beyond the two-letter plays, X appears in an enormous range of common English words. The EX- prefix alone gives you EXACTLY (19 pts), EXOTIC (15 pts), EXCLAIM, EXPIRY, and dozens more. X in the middle creates OXYGEN (17 pts), HEXAGON (18 pts), and PIXEL (14 pts). X paired with J in JINX delivers 18 points from just 4 letters — one of the most efficient plays in the game. MAXIMIZE (28 pts) combines X with Z for the ultimate premium tile pairing. The key to X mastery is recognizing that you should never settle for just AX or OX when better options exist — but you should also never waste time searching when the board demands a quick tactical play.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Four two-letter fallbacks:</strong> AX, EX, OX, XI — all score 9 points. X is never stuck because you always have a 9-point minimum play available.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>JINX is the most efficient X word:</strong> 18 points in 4 letters = 4.5 pts/letter. It pairs X with J for a devastating short play that fits tight positions.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>X on premium squares:</strong> X on DLS = 16 points, X on TLS = 24 points from one tile. Short X words like AX and OX are perfect for reaching these squares.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>EX- prefix is your best friend:</strong> EXACTLY, EXOTIC, EXCLAIM, EXPIRY — the EX- prefix opens up dozens of options from common rack letters.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Never exchange X:</strong> With four 9-point two-letter plays always available, there's never a reason to exchange X. Hold it for premium square access.</span></li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-scrabble-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Scrabble Words Ever — Ultimate List</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-x/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Containing X — Top Scoring X Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-j-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best J Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring J Plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/shortest-words-with-x/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Shortest Words With X — High-Value X Plays for Scrabble</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
